The trap many people fall into is thinking if they can't carve out an hour for exercise, then it's not worth doing. 

"I am too busy to exercise. Between work and kids and school and [insert a billion other reasons], I just don't have the time." 

I get it. 

If you're pressed for time, let me introduce you to "chunking." You're taking an activity and breaking it into smaller chunks.

We might not have a full 60-minute stretch to take a walk, but...four 15-minute strolls? Probably. Or how about starting with two 15-minute walks? 

Think about the activity you want to do and see how you can slice it up, and fit it into your daily schedule. 

The short workout we do always beats the long workout we never do.
